title: World Lost
description:
Who knew humanity would be playing Hide-and-Seek with cannibalistic maniacs as the seekers. I don't know what I did to deserve something that went as far as the end of the world; what any of us humans had done. A world that once had a future in store now had fallen into a world without hope. Without peace. A world that was lost. 

Maybe we had driven the world to what lie beneath the iceberg ourselves. Maybe mad scientists fooled around too much. The truth was that no one knew, and probably would ever know. One thing is for sure, though. I would not live another day just to be turned into a murderer. I will survive in the world with no future; the world lost among itself.

title: La Douleur Exquise || Min Yoongi
description:
La Douleur Exquise
(lit) Exquisite Pain
(n.) the heart-wrenching pain of wanting the affection of someone unattainable


Being a very rare alpha female werewolf has always made your life difficult and the last thing you needed was catching feelings for one of your fellow alpha pack members when it's painfully clear that not only does he not reciprocate those feelings but he has them towards someone else. It's true what they say - love is blind and, in your case, borderline foolish but you remain by his side as a friend, slowly dying on the inside. The question is - how long can you keep that up?

Y/N:  "He looked happy..." you sighed "... and it hurts."
Taehyung:  "I know, sweetheart, I know..." he said, gently cradling you "I'm so sorry."

Hoseok:  "Rogue alpha. Y/N was attacked.

Y/N:  "You're getting a mate. Why is it so wrong for me to get one too, Yoongi?"
Yoongi: "What do you plan on doing - fucking every man in this bar? That's really cheap of you, Y/N."

Y/N: "I'm done torturing myself. From now on... I come first."

Jin:  "Yoongi needs you."
Y/N:  "I can't help you. He's on his own."

Yoongi:  "I'm sorry..."
Namjoon:  "You say that a lot lately... but it might be too late."

How much can one endure in the name of love before they realize that some things just aren't meant to be?


A/N:  Please, note the story might contain mentions of and/or mature content, rough language and might not be appropriate for readers below a certain age. You've been warned :)
I've been writing for a while now but this story is particularly close to my heart. I decided to post it because of my cousin and the encouragement I got from my sisters from different misters (ok, that was bad) Souka, Fran, Vasi and Eva. I will link their profile if they give me their permission. For now - enjoy, comment and vote if you like it ^^

description:

When 15-year-old Camilla Johnson's twin sister, K.J goes missing, it causes uncertainty and agony throughout the neighborhood. When a body that appears to be her sisters is found floating in a nearby lake, Cami chooses not to accept the authenticity of her sister is death, but nobody else believes what she has to say... nobody except for Justin Stuart, Ronnie McLean, and Cameron Rodriguez. title: The Search for Happiness (The Hobbit Fanfiction)
description: Mia is one of the last skin-changers to ever exist. title: Life Isn't How It Seems
description:
"You don't understand Jacob!  I love you, and as weird as that sounds coming from me,  I'm being one hundred and ten percent honest.  I have never once loved someone more in my lif-" Ally tried to say, but Jacob cut her off with a passionate kiss. 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Jacob is a screwed up boy,  he's never had friends,  he doesn't talk,  he doesnt go to school, he dropped school to work instead, and when he goes home he plays his piano.  His life at home is not the best,  he hates it, he wants to escape, but after he meets this girl, his life changes, Jacob seems, happier? What is this feeling? He's never felt anything other than pain, regret, hate,  and depression, but happiness? 

Ally is the complete opposite of Jacob, she's happy,  she has plenty of friends at school, she loves music.  She's never felt sadness, or regret, or pain. When she meets Jacob, her life changes, she wants to help him, but he refuses help. She connects with him, and they grow great affection towards each other. 

But something happens to Jacob and Ally,  they become lost, she pushes away all of her friends, she loses connection with her family, and keeps herself locked up in her room. Did she change for the better? Or did she change for the worse?

title: Captured and Loved By The Unknown Wolf
description:
"I loved you and you were taken and hidden from me." He said. "But now I am back and I am not letting you out of my sight."

I glared at him. I thought I had gotten rid of him long ago. But he's back and still wants the same thing. This guy can't take a hint.

"I have news for you. I have a Mate. I am not interested." I said.

He smiled and said "Oh you are cute when you're mad. That's what I love about you, sweetheart."

I have had just about enough of him. I shifted into my wolf form and I ran at him.

----------------------------------------------------------

Aria has left her old pack with her Mate, Lucas Moon. He is the Alpha and she is his Luna. 

Aria has been through a lot the last few years and has met and defeated many enemies. She is the best fighter and never runs from a fight. She's even come from the edge of death. 

Lucas is the Alpha of The Moon Pack. With Aria now in his life, everything is perfect. But ever since she came back from the edge of death, she hasn't been the same. And on top of that, there is an enemy who puts Lucas's pack and Lucas's title as Alpha, to the test.

In a story where old memories are remembered and old faces are known. Aria and Lucas will have to be on the alert. Ladies and Gentlemen. I present the sequel to "My Past Mate Rejected Me."

title: Cronos: The Orion Project
description: Humanity is the edge of extinction. An alpha predator, known as Chimeras, has made its claim to the lands as the top of the food chain devouring all those unlucky enough to cross its path. Zenith claims its spot as the foremost advanced on the planet with Atrium as its competitor, while Carshire is far behind either but has delved into the unknown and have come out as masters of the elements. Devon Thorne was born outside of the Capital of Atrium in the far away town of Serenity. In the chaos and confusion of a Chimera attack, he and his sister, Rose, are taken and drafted into a program started by the world renowned scientist, Doctor Johnathan Seraph, to create the next generation of warriors. Like all things, they are not as they seem and Devon must find his way out of a possible civil war, with him and his sister at the center of it.

Have you ever heard that our lives are intertwined, by two people linked to another, even if we don't know we exist, young and old we effect then somehow. title: My Ex Nextdoor
description:
Ano ang mararamdaman mo 'pag iniwan ka ng paasa mong boyfriend na wala man lang sinabing dahilan sa'yo? Well, 95% sure na magagalit ka 'diba?

Syempre, sino nga ba naman ang hindi magagalit 'pag iniwan ka na lang ng boyfriend mo sa ere. Pero ika nga nila, 'Love is in the air' daw kaya tayo iniiwan ng magagaling nating boyfriend pero hindi naman talaga literal ang ibig sabihin nun. 

Nakakainis lang kasi minahal natin sila ng PAK na PAK pero iniwan lang tayo ng GANERN GANERN lang. Aminin niyo, minsan nyo na ring naisipan na basagin ang kaligayahan ng boyfriend niyo at gawing scramble egg saka ipakain sa alagang aso ng kapit bahay niyo para lang maramdaman nila ang sakit na ibinigay nila sa inyo, right? Minsan niyo na rin hinihiling na sana mawala na sila sa mundong 'to o 'di kaya sana hindi nyo na makikita ang pangit na pag-mumukha ng boyfriend nyo, right? 

Pero what if isang araw... Magigising ka na lang at magugulat na kapit bahay mo na pala ang isang lalake na kinamumuhian mo sa buong buhay mo? Hmmm. Ano kaya ang mararamdaman mo? 

Kung kailan 100% sure na moved on ka na, bigla-bigla na lang susulpot ang paasa mong boyfriend. Sarap bayagan ano? 

Anyways, napapahaba na ang description ng storyang ito. 

Oh siya. Simulan niyo ng basahin ang storyang ito! Enjoy!

Note: Ang storyang ito ay punong-puno ng ka-bitter-an dahil narin sa karanasan ng ating bida na isa sa mga naging sawi ang lovelife at naiwan nang mag-isa sa ere.

title: A Twist in Time [Harry Potter Roleplay]
description:
Okay, this is the last time I'm attempting this. If it dies this time, the idea is gone for good. 

Time flies, seasons change, the world goes on. Time pauses for no one. The future is always coming and the past is always behind us, but what people forget is that time has always been and always will be relative. 

The Marauders' future is the Golden Trio's present, which is the Next Generation's past. They all have a connected destiny. 

Through Voldemort's dark magic, time becomes more confusing and fates aline. The Golden Trio's Era finds itself together with the Mauraders and the Next Gen. They all exist together, outside of time. How will people react? What will happen next? Or perhaps, it's already happened.

title: Unexpected - Candice LeRae Story
description:
The life of a wrestler can be hectic, the constant traveling, constant bumps being taken in the ring, the mental toll it takes on you to be able to keep a life outside of the squared circle is sometimes even worse than the physical pain. 

Being a woman in this business is also very difficult, not to many women in the world can keep up with and sometimes be better than the men. However there was one petite little blonde who could hold her own very well inside and outside of the ring. 

Candice Lerae, that name is known around the world to wrestling fans. She is small but fierce, she won't let you off easy. As tough as she may seem on the outside on the inside there's still the shy quiet little girl who is just living her dream. 

That toughness is about to be put to the test when she comes face to face with the mini version of herself that she thought she'd never see again.. the mini me she had given up 6 years prior..

title: Moving On.
description:
This was not supposed to happen, they were not supposed to meet. An angry young Pashtun with his ego problems was not supposed to fall for the Americanized version of a Pakistani Muhajir, hack life was not decided for love, not for him at least.
He was hard headed than why his gray orbs sudden soften for the brown ones. He had decided that he will marry the first girl that came in front of him to prove a point to his theoretically former tribal bride and in laws. But it took a highway route when he saw a certain, lost girl at the Jinnah Airport. A girl in white cotton floor length dress with a brown leather jacket with a pair of converse munching on a packet of lays masala, sitting on her own trolley, flipping her head here and there as her scarf moved with her without even for once being displaced from its original position.
Was he ready to marry a girl that he does not know let alone liked by first sight when he knew in his family approval comes from the elders where there is no choice left for them, the broods? He might be an introvert and an honor preserving chap but he was clear when it came to what he wants and needs. He never confused his feelings with his duties as the head of his family or as the impending head of the chief of his tribe, to be the next Emir of Gorgush. 
Olasyar Khan, was in that state of mind but then why did his heart feel that pine? He was ready to make everything turn according to his desires, the Pashtun in him was not ready to back down and let others lead his life for him. Allah showed him the way, so he will move all the rocks and stones in his path even if he must pick them up by his bare hands.
As the tag on the bag read the name, he uttered the last words and left, "Zareen Wadi, be ready to be Zareen Khan."
Their fates were already amalgamated, they just had to find their way to each other.

title: The Secret of Drulea Cottage
description:
"I shall always love you, my dear bairn. Remember that, no matter what happens. And you must promise me something before I go," Bethany whispered with all the strength she could muster.

"Anything, Mum," the young woman answered.

"You must stay away from the water."

"I promise."

The year is 1759. Briony Fairborn, midwife of Everton, struggles to find acceptance after her mother's death while living in a town that ostracizes her for her scandalous origins. Her family has always been shrouded in mystery, ever since her great-grandmother first came to the small town in Orkney. With only one friend in the world, she has little hope of gaining any others, let alone finding a husband. Her life seems set on a straight course without any room for wavering.

That is, until an unexpected ship finds its way to Everton's port.

Suddenly, Briony's life becomes much more complicated. These newcomers are hiding something, and Briony soon discovers that they are not the only ones. A strange man named Niall Moreland arrives in town, a man who offers Briony the acceptance she craves. But does he know something about her family that she doesn't?

And what about the charming owner of the ship, Santiago Mendes? His interest in Briony seems to go beyond mere friendship, but could he ever love someone like her?

As Briony seeks the truth, the secrets of her heritage begin to unravel. Secrets that she may not be ready to face.

*If there is a an exclamation mark and a box, it means "l." My phone has a glitch.*
Mira Claiborne's life is not perfect. It's the farthest thing from, actually. Nobody in her family shared her beliefs on religion, death, and the afterlife.
As her brother lies in a hospital bed suffering from leukemia, she is determined to complete everything she's every wanted to do with a newfound appreciation for life.
When she teams up with her best friend and a new boy in her sophomore year, she discovers revenge, happiness, and the adrenaline of accomplishment.
Together they embark on a journey to complete the list, which includes trespassing, getting back at her bullies, and risking their lives. Can they complete the list and make it out unharmed? Even if she has no more siblings and her family hates her, Mira knows that things should play out.

title: Against Her Wishes
description:
"You should be grateful for this opportunity, Charlotte. That is another thing you'll learn some day." She said, and I knew she meant to end the conversation on that note. I no longer wanted to be in her presence anyways, but my legs refused to carry me away from the woman I used to admire. My mother was my rock, the one I could count on to stick up for me in any way possible. We struggled through everything together. Now, I could hardly look at her without scowling. 
     "Thank you, Mother, for accepting the opportunity to sign away my life. I'm sure I'll be grateful someday, if I haven't already killed myself." I said, then quickly turned on my heel and stormed out of the room. I could hardly see through the blind rage that clouded my vision, but I managed to get into my room, lock the door, and throw myself face first onto my still unmade bed.
     Letting out the sob I'd been holding in, my body violently shook as I cried for the first time since my father had died. Never have I felt there to be a reason to feel so weak, until now. Knowing that my fate was sealed to a man whom I've never met made my stomach throb and throat constrict painfully. In the end, this was be the only thing my mother ever raised me for after all. And that revelation was the hardest part to swallow. 
***
February 27, 1845
     After attending the illustrious Woodvale ball, Charlotte is given devastating and life altering news that changes her own predetermined path forever. Except, this decision doesn't come without its consequences. Follow a young woman as she struggles to grow close to someone she feels she shouldn't have affection towards, whilst also learning to love herself in return. Yet, tragedy and incredible heartbreak still lurk in the depths of Charlotte's uncertain future...

description:
I am a princess, moreover, I am a fool of a princess.

Born in the imperial palace, my appearance is as average as that of the white radish and cabbages in the fields. Throughout the four seasons of the year, my face is always displaying a dull expression, eyes forever shrouded in haze.

Including hers, his, and theirs.

Just leisurely living my days comfortably in the palace like this, I firmly believe I can continue to play dumb to the end.

"Where do you think you are going?" Locaine's lips are mere inches from my ear. A shiver traveling from the base of my spine to the strait of my neck at his hypnotic voice.

"I don't want to play this type of game with you," my voice falters briefly, thoughts raking through my mind at the many possibilities to the outcome of succumbing to him. 

Locaine backs off me more or less, only to toss me around, pushing my back up against the door. His sculpted chest presses against mine as he flashes me a coy smile, "I haven't even explained the game yet and you already want to leave."

Thalia and her brother arrive at Daphne's and she claims she's one of the other Oracles.  Next comes Meg and with all three girls together they set out one a dangerous quest that could save them, but bring the downfall of the gods themselves.  Will they make it or will the gods or the curse take them out before that can happen?

title: The Unseen Immortal
description:
Blood. Pain. War. Those three words described his life. He never had the greed that tainted the good men of his city. And yet, he still suffered the consequences.

Perseus was a young peasant of the city, Athens. It was one of the last still Greek cities still standing. His mother was gone; she died during battle. The Persians had raided their city, leaving rubble and smoke. 

Now, Perseus had run, not because he was a coward, but to save what little he had left. His little sister.

They were different. That much their mother had told them. They were set apart. Even from each other. 

Perseus was a son of a Lelantos, the Titan of Air and Hunting. 

Phoebe, Percy's sister, was a daughter of Poseidon, the Olympian God of the Sea.

Perseus fought for his sister. Nearly died for her several times. 

Until he failed.

He was left desolate, empty, and alone.

But maybe it was for the better.

title: Hunk
description:
"Go to my room and wait for me there." His words kept playing in my mind like a CD. I was now in his room, everything was dark outside and inside too. Nobody knew I was here except for Aiden. I've no idea why he wanted me in his room when his girlfriend was sitting right next to him. I had my back facing the door and suddenly I felt someone closing the door and walking near me. My heart dropped in my stomach when I turned and suddenly found myself being pushed on the wall.

"Wh---" I tried to ask while shaking uncontrollably but his beautiful hawk eyes shut me up. 

"Why were you looking at my lips in the party?" His question shook me, I didn't know he notice. I didn't mean to but he was my long time crush and it takes time to crush those feelings. 

"i--" I stammered,

"You wanna taste them?" he walked closer, keeping his hands on the wall and locking me inside his arms, we were barely an inch away. "tell me you want that." there was a smirk on his face and suddenly it disappeared  when he looked at my lips and gulped. All I knew was that he had rejected me,  hurt me and now this? when he is already dating his long time love. 

"I'm allowing you." his words choice was terrific, giving me goosebumps. 



He pulled a bit more closer and slowly brushed his lips against mine, giving me electrifying chills down my spine. 

"please do--" I tried to stop it but I knew if I resisted he was going to make my life living hell. 

"Do you want more?" he narrowed his eyes, licking his lips. "And if you told this to anyone, girl you are doomed." He warned, I knew his punishments and it scared me.

"I won--" I tried to talk but he pulled his body more closer, touching against mine. 

"Tonight you will please me." He blew an air on my lips and frozed my whole world. Why would he want me to do that? He had his girlfriend here. My whole body started trembling in fear.

title: A Piccolo Love Story ‚ù§ (Lemon)
description:
Writing about a female Saiyan that has been on earth, but not known of. She did not know what a Saiyan was. All she knew was that she was a little different, and....has a tail. Sooner or later she runs into one of the Z Fighters and starts to form a close relationship with him... 
then she's introduced to the rest of the Z Fighters and is enlightened on her race. She becomes friends with the fighters and starts training with a certain someone, whom she starts developing feelings towards. And the other developing the same kind of sensational feelings that were unknown to him.

The past few years have been tough, especially for the Z Warriors. 
This group of fighters consisted of several strong men. 
Goku, vegeta, gohan, trunks, tien, krillin, yamcha, chiaotzu, and piccolo. 
Over the years they've battled extraordinary opponents, who have decided to try and destroy there home. Battle after battles, no breaks.
It was almost like there planet was a magnet of some sort, always attracting evil. 
These last several months it's been so quiet, and peaceful. 
This was the first break from evil the Z fighters have had in a while, all of them wishing this silence could last a life time. 
Most of the fighters took this opportunity to be lazy and slack off from training. 
Others like piccolo, and vegeta where not ones to lay back and do nothing all day. Every day they would train, if givin the chance and strengthen there body's to the maximum. 
Vegeta was very...picky? He chose to be in solitude, inside of a gravity chamber. Working his body until his muscles were torn to shreds. 
Piccolo on the other hand would always look for new ways and places to train his Mind and body, but never over worked himself to the point it would take weeks for his body to re cooperate. To him it was just a wast of time and energy.

title: The Golden Year- The Sorceress
description:
None of us can choose our destiny  but nobody can escape it either...
In this world of magic and chaos, Leila was left an orphan having no one left after a tragic fire. Over the years she learns how to use all sorts of weapons; the once sweet little girl had grown up to be a dangerous woman that didn't trust anyone. But things change drastically when Leila turns sixteen-years old and she is forced to serve the golden year.

The golden year gives the opportunity to escape the life laid out for them since birth. But Leila sees it as a nightmare. It means turning her back on her secret love, Theo. However, Leila begins to doubt her original assumptions when she gets to know Prince Leonardo.

She is pulled into the heart of a war between kingdoms at odds. She soon discovers her magical gifts and her destiny as the 'chosen one'. She never expects to learn a new truth about her own parents and about herself.  In this sweeping fantasy about Leila's journey to fulfill her destiny and all the monsters that stand in her way. Yza Blade is your typical high-school student, whose fate encounter with the "Stardust Knight" clan changes his life forever in ways that cannot be explained. title: The hunger games (Genderbend) -1
description:
Winning will make you famous.
Losing means certain death.

The nation of Panem, formed from a post-apocalyptic North America, is a country that consists of a wealthy Capitol region surrounded by 12 poorer districts. Early in its history, a rebellion led by a 13th district against the Capitol resulted in its destruction and the creation of an annual televised event known as the Hunger Games. In punishment, and as a reminder of the power and grace of the Capitol, each district must yield one boy and one girl between the ages of 12 and 18 through a lottery system to participate in the games. The 'tributes' are chosen during the annual Reaping and are forced to fight to the death, leaving only one survivor to claim victory.

When 16-year-old Stiles's young brother, Whitemore, is selected as District 12's male representative, Stiles volunteers to take his place. He and his female counterpart Annabeth, are pitted against bigger, stronger representatives, some of whom have trained for this their whole lives... , he sees it as a death sentence. But Stiles has been close to death before. For him, survival is second nature.

title: Butcher Bert & the Monkey Mafia
description:
There is no greengrocer in Springvale. No bakery or fish shop. There isn't even a milk bar. One-by-one they've been put out of business by supermarket mogul Sal Monella and his farting monkeys.

Only one competitor remains: Bert's Quality Meats.

Bert has owned his shop for forty years, and he's not going to sell without a fight.

So begins an epic retail war: between Sal and his monkeys, and Butcher Bert and his resourceful Viet cleanup kid Kim. Sal will stop at nothing, even if it means seducing Kim's prune-eating school teacher, in a steamy scene that will have you reaching for the nearest bucket. 

Springvale will never be the same again.

FOR FANS OF
David Walliams
Andy Griffiths
Roald Dahl
Charles Darwin

READERSHIP
Ages 7 to 10, or anyone who enjoys a good fart joke.

title: The Minetti Horror Twins
description:
Given up for adoption the day they were born, Tito and Vito Minetti spend the next six years in the foster care system, bouncing in and out of houses of families unfit for the twins. In 2004, shortly after the boys turn six, they pack up what few belongings they have and run away.

On the run for three days, they're in need of food and water. A man finds the boys and takes them in, raising them outside of the darkness and secrets of his own life. It isn't until five years later when the boys save the man's life that he finally gives them what they've been asking for: a way into the Lucchese crime family.

Every killer comes from somewhere, and this is only the beginning for the Minetti boys.

title: Inseparable Love
description:
"You can't touch me!" He said with tear filled eyes.
"Please." I said with so much longing the word was left almost incoherent.
  He turned his back on me and started to walk away rigidly and my heart twisted resulting in me pouncing from my spot to grab him. 
  Hearing the rustling from behind him he turned his head to the left just as I was about to make contact. 
   I went right through him and fell with a thud on the ground. Everything went black then.
   


      On a certain day when Bexley Wells is 11 she begins to see things that no one else can see, but ignores it because her abusive mother has convinced her that she is insane.
       On one fateful day she chooses to run away only to be stopped by a boy who knows something about her that she is clueless about. 
       Juggling school, work, home life, boys and her friends isn't as easy as it sounds with Bex.
       She will follow the pale boy with overgrown black hair and seemingly limitless pools of dark shining blue eyes anywhere, but even some people have their limits. 
Will Bex let those deathly limits stop her from finding out who she truly is or conquer who she is told to be and changed for the better or worse?

title: Something Special Between Friends (MCSM)
description:
"No....... Sky please don't leave me like this....... I love you more than anything in this world." Miana whispered softly to the baby wolf in her lap. 

Sky did nothing by look up at her and whimper, his injuries only getting worse. 

Miana knew within seconds that he couldn't be saved...... that it was over for him.

She set him down and patted his white and grey head one last time before hearing a final whimper from him. 

"It's okay, boy. You did good..... just rest..... I love you, Sky." She whispered before letting tears slip past her teal eyes and run down her pale cheeks, streaking them with red as she looked away. She couldn't help it. None of this felt real, and yet..... there he was.... the wolf she had taken care of since he landed on her doorstep..... gone.

But then again, is what we feel always what we see?

title: Convince Me Alpha
description:
Prologue 

Running since I was twelve. Never staying in one place for too long, knowing they're looking for me. I wish my parents were here. I miss them terribly, leaving me alone with no one to be there for me.
Riley has been running for five years, knowing no where is safe for her. Her parents murdered by The Order, a group created long ago to destroy shifters. Walking late at night, her running stops when she walks into a cop and sees that she's a street kid. Riley is put into the system and sent to a foster home, staying silent and telling no one nothing about her life.
Entering a new school in the middle of the year as an eleventh grader, Riley works hard to learn what she can and even has a few friends whom she street dances with while determining how long she can stay till they catch up wit her. The last thing she expected was finding her mate. Now she has a tough decision to make. Accept her mate who is the Alpha, or continue to run?

Convince me dear Alpha to stay or I'll run...

title: Death is My Name
description:
Corvus, a young girl, is ecstatic when she learns that she'll be taking on her father's previous occupation as Death, collector of Souls and Wielder of the Scythe. But, who would've know all the troubles the thing could bring her, not to mention her sudden mood swings and detachment from the outside world?

To go along with her ever growing ward of troubles, a mysterious force has been taking the lives of innocent people, increasing the death rate by loads and wrecking havoc in the world above and beneath. Tired of being accused of being the source and quite possibly ready to kill everyone herself, Corvus takes off to find the one who's been limiting her already limited free time and getting her in trouble. Can't say she particularly likes the idea of two nosy, human teen girls tagging along as well as a stubborn Angel who's hell bent on turning her in. Can't forget the mischievous demon. Throw that in there too.

But, despite being the "Collector Of Souls," is it possible that she might be the one collecting her own?

title: By Your Side
description:
When Angel Miller finds himself accidentally locked in the library for an entire weekend, he doesn't think things could get any worse. But that's before he realizes that Dax Miller is locked with him.  Angel doesn't know much about Dax except that he's trouble.  Between the rumors about the fight he was in (and that brief stint in juvie that followed it) and his reputation as a loner, he's not exactly the ideal person to be stuck with. Still, Angel just keeps reminding himself that it is only a matter of time before Jeff, his almost-boyfriend, realizes that he left him in the library and comes to rescue him.

Only he doesn't come. No one does.

Instead it becomes clear that Angel is going to have to spend the next couple of days living off vending-machine food and making conversation with a boy who clearly wants nothing to do with him. Except there is more to Dax than meets the eye. As he and Angel at first grudgingly, and then not so grudgingly, open up to each other, Angel is struck by their surprising connection. But can their feelings for each other survive once the weekend is over and Angel's old life, and old love interest, threaten to pull him from Dax's side?

I do not own this story, this belongs to Kasie West, I am using the exact same words as she did in the original story, except for some pronouns and I switched out one of her characters for one of my originals, Angel. I basically just made this book gay. I am not making any money off of this story, it is just for pure fun, and like I said, this story belongs to Kasie West. By the way, the cover I am usig is the original, and that also belongs to Kasie West.

(Yes. Pregnant by Luke Hemmings. One of many. I know. But this one is different. I'm a sucker for conflict stories and every 5sos baby story that I've read has been everything but that. Some have gotten close but they were always too quick at giving in. So for all you conflict junkies out there. This story is just for you.)

"I'm sorry, Em. But I think it's best if we weren't together anymore."
That was the last thing he said to me before he walked away. That was the day I tried to tell him that I was pregnant by him. 
My name Is Emily Yates and the one I was talking about is Luke Hemmings. Yes from 5 seconds of summer.

title: Beasts & Burdens (An MC Romance)
description:
"Sarin, someday you'll realize that the moment those lips claimed mine I decided that I'd tear Heaven and Hell apart, just to find my way back to you. You're the kinda girl they write fairytales about."

Sarin Heyman is a princess in a world full of leather and motorcycles. She's the daughter of the infamous "Beast" Heyman, President of the Nightmare Assassins MC in North Carolina. A tattooer at her club's shop, Sarin, has lived the last four years of her life by one motto: Live free, but never expose your heart again.

Levi "Phantom" James, is the proverbial golden boy of the Devil's Henchmen MC. Gone away for four long years, Phantom finally returns to his hometown of Northridge, North Carolina. A full patched member of his father's MC and their new Treasurer, Phantom has the kingdom at his fingertips. 

There's only one catch: Northridge is also home to his club's bitter rivals, the N.A., and the only girl he's ever loved.

When the two rival clubs are forced to draw a truce to protect Sarin from a vicious group looking to invade the territory, and the entire foundation their world is built on, will Levi go in feet first or fall head over heels again? 

Can Sarin and Levi put everything they've been taught behind them for the sake of rekindling their love or will their blood keep them forever apart?

Not all fairytales are easy, especially when there are dragons at every turn.

*This is a dark romance, set in the outlaw MC world. Contains moments of mature language and situations.*

title: If the Shoe Fits
description:
"I am NOT a goody two shoes!" I snap, glaring at Prince Charming.

   "Hey, if the shoe fits, wear it." He says, shrugging. "You of all people should know that, Cinderella." He smirks, taking a step closer to me.

   "If you turn around, I'll show you where my shoe fits." I growl, pulling up my dress to show off my menacing glass slippers.

   He just laughs, running a hand through his dark curls. "Sorry to burst your bubble, princess, but those are made of plastic. You couldn't hurt me if you tried."

   "I hate Disney World." I growl bitterly, smoothing out my costume. Prince Charming gasps, placing a hand over his heart in mock surprise. "Are you telling me you're unhappy at the Happiest Place on Earth?"

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ cover by the amazing @thatbeliever

    Do you know the worst thing about working at Disney World is? Have you ever smiled so much you've pulled a muscle? Have you ever played truth or dare with Aladdin or eaten so many dole whips you think you might puke?

Neither has Cassy Jones. But she's about too.

When Cassy gets a summer job at Disney playing Cinderella, she figures it'll be a cake walk. It can't be that hard to smile and wave at a few kids everyday, right?

Wrong. With weather in the 100's, bratty kids pulling on her dress, and her ever obnoxious co-star Prince Charming, Cassy is about to find out how unhappy the happiest place on Earth can be.

title: Irish Turquoise
description:
Brooke Wright has always been the tomboy type. But, all of her friends are girly girls. They think that you have to dumb yourself down for popularity. The truth is, Brooke never even wanted to be popular in the first place, because when you attend Lilian High School, everybody thinks that you can only be two things: 

1.) Popular and dumb

or 

2.) Unpopular and smart 

Usually when you make a sports team, you're considered popular. 

Usually when you get an award every year for good grades, you're considered unpopular. 

The popular and unpopular people would almost never talk or hang out.

That's just how things worked at Lilian High School.

But what happens when Brooke begins to have a very close friendship with one of the unpopular people named Luke Wood? 

What happens when their close relationship takes a sharp turn? 

Will the popular turn their backs on her for befriending an unpopular? 

Will the unpopular turn their backs on Luke for befriending a popular?

We'll just have to see.........
